         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/9/61 ¶ Dear Dr Hooker. ¶  ¶ Enclosed a letter from Dr Harvey and byefollowing my reply. I thought you would like to read this correspondence, as you desired Dr Harvey to adress me on the subject, t...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">61.09.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, 1858-70, un-numbered letter after f. 48.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS black-edged; M's sister Bertha died 7 September 1861.</p>
               </note>24/9/61</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Dr Hooker.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Enclosed a letter from Dr Harvey and byefollowing my reply. I thought you would like to read this correspondence, as you desired Dr Harvey to adress me on the subject, to which it mainly alludes.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found; but see W. Harvey to J. Hooker, May 1861 (in this edition as M61-05-00), and J. Hooker to M, 14 July 1861.</p>
               </note> I have suffered from bronchial inflammation this winter, but with the returning warm weather I am just recovering health. I trust your worthy incomparable father will now be again in the enjoyment of health. What a blessing to him, that he can depend on you so fully in everything.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to enclose a copy of my letter to the Secr. of the R.S. Will you be so kind to present it, in case the original had not reached?<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Letters not found. However, at its meeting 24 October 1861 the Council of the Royal Society resolved: 'That Mr Ferdinand Müller, now in Australia, be granted an extension of the time of his admission into the Society during his stay abroad. (Minutes of the Council of the Royal Society, Printed, vol. 3, London, 1870, pp. 100-1).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am sorry, that Mr Bentham still continues as on former occasions to publish herbarium names. As long as a plant was not published with a diagnosis, I do not think any reference should be taken to a temporary name, altho' such a name may have appeared in print. Thus <name key="Cocculus%20Hookeri">Cocculus Hookeri</name> which I saw originally only in fruit was reduced by myself to <name key="Stephania">Stephania</name> long ago, as reference to various of my essays (L.S. &amp;c) will show.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See Lucas (1995) for discussion of M's complaints about excessive synonomy based on manuscript names. M mentioned <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cocculus%20Hookeri">Cocculus Hookeri</name>anus</seg> without description in B56.02.01; it is not clear where M ‘reduced’ this to <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Stephania">Stephania</name>
                     </seg>; he mentioned <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Stephania">Stephania</name>
                     </seg> without reference to an earlier name in B58.05.01, p. 141. <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Bentham (1861) wrote: 'In Australia only four Menispermaceae are as yet known, two of them, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Pericampylus incanus</seg> Miers (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">Cocculus Moorei</seg>, F. Muell., <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Fragm. Phyt. Austr</seg>. 1. 162) and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Stephania">Stephania</name> hernandiaefolia</seg>, Walp. (<seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. australis</seg> and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">S. Gaudichaudi</seg>, A. Gray, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Bot. Amer. Expl. Exped</seg>. v. i. pp. 37, 38; <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Cocculus%20Hookeri">Cocculus Hookeri</name>anus</seg>, F. Muell. MSS.), are widely spread Asiatic species' (p. 52).</p>
               </note>
               <name key="Citrus%20Australasica">Citrus Australasica</name> is published by me first in the Fragmenta I, 26, Jun 1858.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>B58.06.01, p. 26.</p>
               </note> I have the ripe fruit.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>These are my herbarium notes on it: Fructus ellipsoidius 1-2" longus odore fere citreo praeditus, 6-loculatus, polyspermus. <seg style="">Semina subovata [v.] globoso-ovata 2-3" longa Testa pallide flavida, laevis. Embryo amygdaloideus. Radicula brevissima supera. </seg>Clarence River. Dr Beckler. — We have many excellent articles for the exhibition,<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>International Exhibition, London, 1862.</p>
               </note> about 80 sp timber, mostly in large planks. Also a good many distilled oils (Includ. Pittospor undul.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Pittosporum%20undulatum">Pittosporum undulatum</name>
                     </seg>?</p>
               </note> &amp; <name key="Atherosperma%20moschatum">Atherosperma moschatum</name>) also a fine series of gyps-fruits &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The full series I shall see given to Kew, the duplicates to Edinburgh.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever yours</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Mr Oldfield is gone to Cape Lewin<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Cape Leeuwin, WA? Mr Oldfield … Lewin <seg style="font-style: italic; ">in central margin on front of folio</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray give Mr Bentham &amp; Prof Lindley my respects<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Pray give … respects <seg style="font-style: italic; ">in central margin on back of folio</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Atherosperma%20moschatum">Atherosperma moschatum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Citrus%20Australasica">Citrus Australasica</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Cocculus%20Hookeri">Cocculus Hookeri</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Pittosporum%20undulatum">Pittosporum undulatum</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Stephania">Stephania</name>
            </p>
         </div>
